[thinking] I’m thinking about custom annotations like @SdkPublicApi. Currently, they’re applied to classes only, not to annotation types. But with the new feature, lifecycle or classification annotations can target `TYPE`, which allows them to annotate other annotations. This opens up the possibility for reusable codebase-specific stereotypes. I also note that annotations like @Immutable and @ThreadSafe also target `TYPE`. There's a lot of potential for enhancing how we use annotations here!
