 a constructor that has the @NotNull annotation for its parameters. It feels a bit odd since constructors don’t technically return a value, but they don’t support null values. I wonder if this adds clarity or just complicates things. The syntax is clear, but the semantics might confuse others when it comes to the purpose of the annotation on constructors. I'll have to reflect on the best approach here.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test methods**\\n\\nThe user wants me to analyze existing test methods to see if they provide sufficient coverage and to identify any new functional features that aren’t covered yet. I need to summarize my findings effectively. I might need to look into the issue regarding adding tests to the existing file. I’m considering the public API from \\\"software.amazon.awssdk:annotations\\\" and noting that the @SdkPublicApi annotation can be applied to packages, which seems to be currently missing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering annotation features**\\n\\nI’m thinking about custom annotations like @SdkPublicApi. Currently, they’re applied to classes only, not to annotation types. But with the new feature, lifecycle or classification annotations can target `TYPE`, which allows them to annotate other annotations. This opens up the possibility for reusable codebase-specific stereotypes. I also note that annotations like @Immutable and @ThreadSafe also target `TYPE`. There's a lot of potential for enhancing how we use annotations here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_28iSiN8uYbXp93gvxEif7SS6|fc_096617df6307ccd20169f7883bc250819fb93dd7e46943abff", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/software.amazon.awssdk/annotations/2.34.0/src/test/java/software_amazon_awssdk/annotations/AnnotationsTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n", "newText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void toBuilderIgnoreFieldCanMarkDerivedAccessorMethods() {\n        BuilderBackedModel model = new BuilderBackedModel(\"orders\", \"checksum\");\n\n        assertThat(model.service()).isEqualTo(\"orders\");\n        assertThat(model.transientMetadata()).isEqualTo(\"orders:checksum\");\n    }\n\n    @SdkPublicApi\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void toBuilderIgnoreFieldCanMarkDerivedAccessorMethods() {\n        BuilderBackedModel model = new BuilderBackedModel(\"orders\", \"checksum\");\n\n        assertThat(model.service()).isEqualTo(\"orders\");\n        assertThat(model.transientMetadata()).isEqualTo(\"orders:checksum\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void sdkAnnotationsCanBeComposedIntoReusableTypeStereotypes() {\n        StableEndpoint endpoint = new StableEndpoint(\"s3\", \"us-west-2\");\n\n        assertThat(endpoint.host()).isEqualTo(\"s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com\");\n        assertThat(endpoint.cacheKey()).isEqualTo(\"s3#us-west-2\");\n    }\n\n    @SdkPublicApi\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Generated(\"annotation-type-generator\")\n    @NotNull\n    private @interface NotNullByDefault {\n    }\n\n    @Mutable\n", "newText": "    @Generated(\"annotation-type-generator\")\n    @NotNull\n    private @interface NotNullByDefault {\n    }\n\n    @SdkPublicApi\n    @Immutable\n    @ThreadSafe\n    @Target(ElementType.TYPE)\n    private @interface StableSdkType {\n    }\n\n    @StableSdkType\n    private static final class StableEndpoint {\n        private final String service;\n        private final String region;\n\n        private StableEndpoint(String service, String region) {\n            this.service = service;\n            this.region = region;\n        }\n\n        private String host() {\n            return service + '.' + region + \".amazonaws.com\";\n        }\n\n        private String cacheKey() {\n            return service + '#' + region;\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Mutable\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 819, "output": 3425, "cacheRead": 20480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24724, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777829907158, "responseId": "resp_096617df6307ccd20169f7881394f4819f9e442fed2fa296c0"}}
